I prefer using affermative language to picking language so that go defaults to the correct value. For example, I don't mind an --enable flag that is true by default. It's mostly stylistic and I don't feel strongly but I prefer reading:

```
if enabled { ... }
if !enabled { ... }
```

to:

```
if disabled { ... }
if !disabled { ... }
```

Positive booleans improve readability.

